  <static seed="1380" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions10.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{2t}{t+5}+\frac{10}{t+5}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2, t\ne -5</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{2t}{t+5}+\frac{10}{t+5}} 
      \amp = \frac{{2t+10}}{{t+5}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{2\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)}}{{t+5}} \\
      \amp = {2, t\ne -5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t+5</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {-5}</m>.</p>
</solution>
